8/19/22, 19:10 - +91 78926 69254: “Goodbyes, they often come in waves.” 

We are sure it would have been a rollercoaster ride entering the college, finally getting to brag about being an IITian but we are sure IIT Hyderabad was much more than just the tag. We are very grateful for all the memories and fun we had together. 

Here's our small attempt to etch IITH in your memories - Farewell video!!

https://youtu.be/6EPRFSKudj8

PS: The video will premiere at 7:30PM.

9/23/22, 23:36 - +91 95004 55420: Hey there, folks!

The Quiz Club, IITH in collaboration with BITS Hyderabad (BPHC) will be conducting a one-of-a-kind Finance Quiz: The FIN-ATC Quiz. This is an open quiz sponsored by OnFinance, a fintech startup aiming to improve financial literacy.

The preliminaries for this Quiz would be held on our campus, with the final round at BITS Pilani, Hyderabad Campus. Each team can comprise of 2 or 3 members. The top 6 teams from the preliminaries, along with 3 additional teams from IITH would advance to the finals, along with other top teams from other preliminaries across Hyderabad. The first place would be awarded ₹5000, followed by the second place with ₹3000 and the third place with ₹2000.

The preliminaries will be conducted in a standard pen and paper format at B114, IITH on 24th September 2022 (Saturday) from 1 PM to 3 PM. 

The finals would be held at BITS Pilani, Hyderabad Campus on 25th September 2022 (Sunday) from 12 PM to 3 PM.

The preliminaries and the finals will be conducted by Quiz Masters from BITS Pilani, Hyderabad Campus.

Interested quizzers can register for the event with the link below:
https://forms.gle/zVZsnFGZjKzVjcKy5
For further details, please find attached the brochure below.

Looking forward to y'all participating!
Regards,
The Quiz Club

9/30/22, 17:58 - +91 90900 72712: Thinking of something to get you occupied this October? Here it is. "INKTOBER".A drawing a day for 31 days.

https://inktober.com/

1) Make a drawing in ink (you can do a pencil under-drawing if you want).

2) Post it*

3) Hashtag it with #inktober and #inktober2022

4) Repeat

Note: you can do it daily, or go the half-marathon route and post every other day, or just do the 5K and post once a week. What ever you decide, just be consistent with it. Inktober is about growing and improving and forming positive habits, so the more you’re consistent the better.

That's it! Now go make something beautiful.

Don't forget to mention Gesture in your posts and stories.

#inktober tober #gesturedrawing #inktober2022
https://www.instagram.com/p/CjIOOYjovVh/?igshid=MDJmNzVkMjY=

10/14/22, 12:49 - +91 90900 72712: It's time for Hyderabad’s biggest and largest student-run Hackathon, Megathon. Megathon is a 24 hour hackathon with participants from all over the country, making it a wonderful platform to interact and collaborate with fellow participants as well as industry experts. Registrations are open right now. 
We, at E-cell IIIT Hyderabad are excited to bring to you a whole range of fun and challenging events to tickle the mind and bring people together to crack mind-boggling tech-based problems with a bit of entrepreneurial flair.  

Winners of the challenges have the chance to attend startup bootcamp at CIE-one of the largest academic incubators in India and to work on their ideas with mentors from esteemed companies. 

Give yourself a chance to come up with innovative solutions to real-world issues and transpose ideas from the drawing-board to the board room. Do not miss out on the opportunity to crack out the big-guns and take risks, as every entrepreneur says, “The biggest risk is to not take risks”. 

Participation is welcome from colleges from all over India. Scan the QR code on the poster or go to megathon.in for registering. 

Exclusive OFFER  Students discount offer: Use the coupon code "EARLYBIRD" for 50% off

10/20/22, 17:10 - +91 90809 60657: Greeting from BTL!

So many films were produced on campus these last few months, its a veritable melting pot of material to learn from.

We will be screening BTL's submission for IFP's (India Film Project) 50 hour filmmaking challenge as well as the various films produced by different hostels for MILAN.

With so many people involved with different tastes and perspectives, it will be interesting to analyse these films.

Join us on October 21st (Friday) at 5:30 PM as we will present a breakdown of all these films.

See you all there!

The Debate Club is excited to bring to you:

          *The Crypto Debate*

Cryptocurrencies were introduced with the intent to revolutionize financial infrastructure, but they have been nothing but rife with grifts, frauds and drug rackets. So it's high time the government steps in to police and regulate the use of cryptocurrency. But can we trust the government to do the right thing? Or is the government taking hasty steps to nip crypto in the bud before it can blossom and subvert fiat money?

*The Motion: The House believes governments should take public steps to disrupt and discourage the use of cryptocurrencies.*

The format is a British Parliamentary Debate. Exciting prizes are to be won! Come join us in *ALH1* at *8:30pm on October 27th*

You can register yourself using: https://forms.gle/zMtgAF5Qx8X6pdVz6

Hope to see you there!!

_Amat Victoria Curam!_

11/1/22, 21:20 - Uchiha(Purli Gnana Abhinav) IIT Hyderabad ES: <Media omitted>
11/1/22, 21:37 - +91 81214 62682: Dear friends, prakriti is back with another interesting event and this is our first techy event this year,
11/1/22, 21:37 - +91 81214 62682: Making of Soil Moisture Sensors. 
Measuring soil moisture is essential for agricultural applications since it allows farmers to manage their irrigation systems better. It is also significantly vital in erosion studies and research. This is an excellent opportunity for you all to make a prototype of the Soil Moisture Sensor and be part of the excitement. We'd love to have you all participate and win exciting prizes.
Further details of the event :
1. You can build any soil moisture sensor you like. We'll be even more delighted to get new prototypes with some advancements.
2. The submission should be in the form of a video presenting the making of the sensor. It's alright if it does not include the entire process. The video must be 2 min or longer. You are also required to submit some photos of the making.
3. You have to submit a description (report) of the working procedure and the components involved, or you can include them in the video. You can mention any advancements or suggestions also.
4. You can approach the EE Lab/Central Workshop for the required components.
5. To get a basic understanding of how to make these sensors do check out this video: https://youtu.be/e6CBy9TMIj0
 
This is an Online Event. Submit your Entries in this form.

The Deadline for the event is 5th Nov 2021.
Prize Money :
1st Place: Rs.1500/-
2nd Place: Rs.1000/-
3rd Place: Rs.500/-

Aero is excited to bring to you,

 _Flight without Formulae_ 

In this fun and interactive session, we will explain the concepts of flight and all the principles that govern them, with as little use of formulae as possible.

12/18/22, 17:33 - +91 96640 72217: *Inter IIT High Prep Problem Statement: Drona Aviation (Aerial Robotics) Team Selection*

Hey all!

We have the second problem statement released for this year's Inter IIT Tech Meet. The problem statement is from the Aerial Robotics domain.

*Problem Statement:*

You may have a look at the problem statement in the link given below.

The problem statement is about *"Drona Aviation: Pluto Drone Swarm Challenge"*

_Problem Statement Link:_ https://interiit-tech.org/images/ps/High_Drona.pdf

*Team Selection:*

If you think you would be able to contribute in solving this problem statement and have previous experience which might be useful for us, then please fill this form. 

A previous experience in the following areas would be really handy:
1. Basics of drones (propellers, motors, pitch, yaw, roll, etc.,)
2. ROS Kinetics
3. OpenCV

_Form Link:_ https://forms.gle/cEfmqU3FrA9rcvYZA

_Deadline to fill the form:_ 5:00 PM, 19th December 2022.

*Logistics:*

1. The maximum team size for this problem statement is 10. 
2. There is no mid-term evaluation.
3. Final Evaluation will be tentatively on 10th February 2023.

*WhatsApp Group Link:*

We'll be discussing all the relevant information related to this problem statement in this WhatsApp group.

_Group Link:_ https://chat.whatsapp.com/Cj9BBJDFtOa9Z6cl8saqao

Also, do join the Overall WhatsApp Group for regular updates about other problem statements as well (Inter IIT Tech Meet 11.0 Overall Group):

_Group Link:_ https://chat.whatsapp.com/GFr4ddB5cVk7uYUVPPMEw7

2/25/23, 15:36 - +91 75694 21250: *Epoch-TL: Vision Quest Hackathon*

Hey all!

We are proud to announce that Epoch is collaborating with TL to organise a Machine Learning Hackathon open to the student community. So ML enthusiasts, put on your thinking hats, and start "networking" away. [ reference to Neural Networks:) ] 

You can find the PS here.

Link: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1fjYSDLiyjajfUuN6uehUYKx39h-_jIzd9TE3wr2FLeY/edit?usp=sharing

Now hold up! We don't want to spoil the entire thing now, do we? The doc shared above is merely a general overview of how the PS would be. We will have an elaborate presentation of the PS, with all the finer details for the ones who register.

So, what are you waiting for? Register here.

Link: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfK3Cs6Qp_GOG9ek6z5fSriI_NhnwXjPTKMI5E0Ccs40bvTnA/viewform?usp=sf_link

 *Deadline: 11:59 PM, 1st March 2023* 

We will have *cash prizes of up to Rs. 5000* for the winners. 

Note that we are also in discussion with Professors to guide this project, so the one with the best model will get a chance to work on the end-to-end implementation of this entire system, under the guidance of a Prof.

P.S. We know B.Tech freshers might be feeling a bit intimidated by the technical details of this problem statement, and wondering if they have what it takes to win. To put these fears to rest, freshers who impress us with their work will get a *special prize on behalf of Epoch and TL* .

Cheers, and hoping to see some great participation!

- Epoch Team & Tinkerer's Lab Team

3/5/23, 23:04 - Abhinav Kompella: <Media omitted>
3/5/23, 23:04 - Abhinav Kompella: Hey everyone,

We are thrilled to announce that Turing Hut, the coding club of VNR VJIET is conducting a national-level coding contest - *TURING CUP*. The contest is designed to test your coding skills, creativity, and problem-solving abilities.

The contest will be conducted in three rounds. The first round will be an online round conducted on 11th March, 2023. The second round and the third round will be held on-site on 25th March 2023, which will be conducted in the VNR VJIET campus, Hyderabad. Accommodation will be provided for teams whose college is not located in Hyderabad.

The contest is open to all the undergraduate students from across the country who are passionate about coding. We encourage you to participate in the contest and showcase your talent.

To participate in the contest, you need to register yourself at Unstop. The registration for the first round will be open until March 8th, 2023. The first round will be conducted online, and the registered participants will receive further instructions via email.

We urge you to register for the contest and showcase your coding skills to the nation. It's an excellent opportunity for you to learn, network, and grow in your career.

To know more: https://turinghut.org/turingcup
Register here: https://unstop.com/o/ue5gaLR?lb=MF8vPuG

Happy coding,
Team Turing Hut.

3/22/23, 18:19 - +91 85780 01808: Join Our Design and Coding Challenge and Win an Exclusive Interview Opportunity | Buildfast

Hi Coders,

We are excited to announce our Web Component Coding Competition, designed exclusively for students like you who are passionate about designing and web development. This competition is a great opportunity for you to showcase your skills and win an interview at a leading startup.

Eligibility:
All Undergrad students who are enthusiastic in Web design/FrontEnd and are currently enrolled in a recognized institution are eligible to participate in this competition.

Competition Details:
The competition involves designing and developing a web component from scratch, which make website development easier and more efficient. The web component can be developed using HTML, CSS, Javascript, and should be compatible with modern browsers. 

Duration: 3 days(6 April 2023 to 9 April 2023 till midnight)

Prizes:
The top three winners will receive a direct interview opportunity at our partner startup, which could be the beginning of an exciting career in tech and, the next top 5 candidates will receive certificate of appreciation. Our partner startups include Ninety-eight entertainment, dreate.Xr, A Design guy 

Judges and Evaluation Criteria:
The entries will be judged by our partner companies' Head of Design and Development team lead. These experts in the field of web design and development will be evaluating the entries based on the following criteria:
* Creativity: How unique and innovative is the web component?
* UI/UX feasibility: Does the web component work as intended and solve the problem it was designed for?
* Coding Best Practices: Are coding best practices followed, including maintainability, readability, and scalability?
* Number of views: No. of views your component gets after it is made live.

Register here:
To participate in the competition, please submit your entry on  https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSczraBvcqAwdEsZyJgktCRH0-FBnhdAeZRsPcieeLxAlel0bQ/viewform by 5 April 2023.

We hope that you will participate in this exciting competition and showcase your web development skills. If you have any questions or clarifications, please do not hesitate to reach out to us at uday@buildfast.co.in We wish you all the best of luck

Regards,
Uday Agarwal
Buildfast Team

We are thrilled to announce that Mr. Manash, the CEO of *Qoptars* , a drone-based startup incubated at *iTIC* , will join us for a talk. Qoptars is a consumer-focused drone company that aims to solve complex problems using drones and UAVs. They serve three aerial application areas: videography, insight, and surveillance. They also integrate AI into their systems' edge, making their products safer, smarter, and better.

During the talk, Mr. Manash will discuss his team's journey of building a startup and offer insights into the drone industry in India. The session will also cover the technical aspects of building a drone, and attendees will see some of Qoptars' products in action.

This is a golden opportunity for both tech enthusiasts and budding entrepreneurs to learn from industry experts about the latest trends and advancements in the drone industry, as well as insights into building a successful startup. Don't miss out on this unique opportunity to gain valuable knowledge and network with professionals in the field. So mark your calendars and make sure to attend the talk

5/10/23, 17:09 - +91 75694 21250: Hello Everyone
Greetings !

Institution's Innovation Council is organizing an Online Talk on "Evolution of Process and Alloy Development Technology in the Past Hundred Years" by Mr. K Ramesh {Vice President (Business Development) at Innomet Advanced Materials Pvt. Ltd., Hyderabad and Former Director (Production and Marketing), Mishra Dhatu Nigam Ltd. (MIDHANI), Hyderabad} to commemorate National Technology Day on 11 May 2023 from 11:30 AM. 

Link to Join the Zoom Meeting - https://us06web.zoom.us/j/87286786293?pwd=US9wMHF5b1Q4Y2ZacmNnZnNxeGZNdz09
Meeting ID: 872 8678 6293
Passcode: 812677

National Technology Day Poster.jpg


Profile of the Speaker

Mr. K. Ramesh superannuated as Director (Production and Marketing) from the illustrious Mishra Dhatu Nigam Ltd.,Hyderabad ,one of the leading metallurgical production units in the country ,developing and manufacturing a range of exotic metals and alloys for ISRO,DRDO, Atomic Energy and Defence. Mr. Ramesh has a  Master's Degree in Metallurgical Engineering from IIT, Bombay and a MBA Degree from Osmania University.  Post retirement, Mr. Ramesh was a Senior Faculty at the Institute of Public Enterprise, Hyderabad, a leading MBA Institute. Mr. Ramesh is presently Vice-President (Business Development) at Innomet Advanced Materials Pvt. Ltd, Hyderabad, one of the reputed Powder Metallurgy manufacturing units in the country.

Request your participation in the online talk being organized to commemorate National Technology Day.

Thank you

Warm Regards

Nakul Parameswar
Convenor, IIC

8/14/23, 11:01 - +91 81800 49566: Namaste 🙏


We hope this email finds you in good health. As we begin our new academic year, get ready to showcase your talent , as we are thrilled to announce the launch of a remarkable initiative that celebrates the rich tapestry of India's cultures and traditions – "Ek Bharat Sanskriti Sangam." 


This initiative, inspired by the theme "The beauty of the world lies in differences, not in similarities" is a celebration of diversity and art. Open to participants aged 18 to 30, it's an opportunity to immerse yourself in the richness of cultures and contribute to the spirit of Ek Bharat Shreshtha Bharat. 


Express your potential and talents, bridging the gaps between cultures within our diverse nation through this social media campaign. 


A few important details are mentioned below. For more information and participation details, visit Ek Bharat Sanskriti Sangam Campaign page. 


Campaign Highlights:

Express Artistry : Showcase your talents in Dance, Singing, Photography and Painting/Sculpting/Sketching.

Embrace Diversity : Perform in art forms from states/UTs other than your home state.

Exciting Rewards : Participants stand a chance to win exciting rewards.

National Platform : Display skills on a national stage.

Use Hashtags : #EkBharatShreshthaBharat #EkBharatSanskritiSangam.
(For category-specific tags, visit the page.)

This is a 3-month campaign divided into 3 phases.There is a list of 12 places (comprising different States and UTs) identified for each phase which the Participants would have to select for their respective performance/act. Please find the list of places for Phase I.


Phase I
Andhra Pradesh ,Arunachal Pradesh, Delhi, Goa, Gujarat, Haryana, Jammu & Kashmir, Ladakh, Meghalaya, Mizoram ,Odisha ,Telangana


Don't miss out on Phase I – the submission window is open now and closes on August 21st, 2023. Upload your entries in the given form.


Rejoice differences, ignite creativity and unleash your talents on a grand stage!

Let's make this campaign a resounding success together. Spread the word and encourage your fellow students to participate wholehearted

Form : https://forms.gle/P4Bw4EMFxGtVjJo46
